      "@type": "Project",
      "schema:legalName": "Mediterranean Ocean Observing System for the Environment - Grande Echelle (MOOSE-GE)",
      "schema:name": "Mediterranean Ocean Observing System for the Environment - Grande Echelle (MOOSE-GE)",
      "schema:url": "https://campagnes.flotteoceanographique.fr/series/235/fr/",
      "schema:description": "The annual MOOSE-GE campaigns, initiated in 2010, are part of the long-term Mediterranean observation network, MOOSE, a network labeled SOERE Allenvi and SNO by INSU in 2016 and 2019. This network The objective of observation is to follow the long-term evolution of the northwestern Mediterranean in the context of climate change and anthropogenic pressure, in order to be able to detect and identify the trend of environmental anomalies in this marine ecosystem. MOOSE thus aims to maintain an integrated and multidisciplinary observation network in the Mediterranean Sea in accordance with the marine infrastructures ILICO, EURO-ARGO and EMSO and the global networks OceanSites and OceanGliders in which MOOSE is involved. \r\nThe objectives of these cruises carried out in 2010, 2011 and 2013 on the Tethys II (INSU), in 2012, 2014, 2015 on the Suroît then in 2016, 2017 and 2018 on the Atalante, and in 2019 and 2021 on Thalassa include: 1) annual maintenance of the 4 LION moorings, DYFAMED on leg 1 then Planier and Lacaze-Duthiers on leg 2 (automatic measurements, particle traps), 2) map and monitor changes in water mass properties, biogeochemical content and zooplankton communities, 3) training for Master M2 Sorbonne University (OACOS, OEM) and ENSTA students, 4) deployment and collection of Argo profiling floats.",
